- In the delta band, opening of the eyes produced significantly greater reductions in frontal and lateral regions, suggesting focal reductions in these regions occurring with, and contributing to, the significant global reduction in delta activity. Theta activity was globally reduced by opening the eyes, but these reductions were significantly larger in posterior regions. Beta reductions from eyes-closed to eyes-open conditions were dominant in posterior and right hemisphere regions, and appeared to be uniquely accompanied by increased activity in frontal hemispheric regions. The balance of this decrease and increase in focal beta activity led to a significant across-scalp average reductions in power with opening of the eyes, but care needs to be exercised in interpreting this statistical result without acknowledgement of its focal basis.
